 The Giraffe

 Animal: Giraffe
 Habitat: semi-arid savannah and savannah woodlands in Africa
 Diet: leaves, buds from tress and shrubs, herbs, vines, flowers, and fruit
 Social Structure: fission-fusion
 Fun Facts:
    1. Giraffes are the tallest mammals on Earth.
    2. Giraffes only need to drink once every few days.
    3. Giraffes only need 5 to 30 minutes of sleep in a 24-hour period.
    4. No two individual giraffes have exactly the same pattern.